    "In November 2022, OpenAI introduced the public with ChatGPT, the Generative Pre-trained Transformer, marking a significant milestone in the landscape of artificial intelligence (AI).",
    "Since its release, ChatGPT has garnered widespread attention and emerged as a representative case study for large language models (LLMs).",
    "As a testament to its impact, an openly acknowledged ChatGPT user at a Swedish university for academic purposes, signaling a potential challenge for educators (Hellerstedt, 2022).",
    "The media discourse surrounding ChatGPT, extensively covered by news outlets such as The BBC (Shearing and McCallum, 2023) and the New York Times (Schulten, 2023), has primarily focused on its mechanics, limitations, and transformative potential in education.",
    "Of particular concern is the influence of ChatGPT on written assessments, raising questions about its advantages, disadvantages, and the future of traditional evaluation methods."
